RACE.RACE_TEXT: MAHONING VALLEY RACE COURSE RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 12200. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.

CLAIM.OWNER: Yoder Susan and Rivera Alan Yahir

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHEN IN ROME tracked the leaders to the turn, waited patiently behind three horse wall of leaders at the quarter pole, angled five wide turning for home and wore down his rivals in a determined well handled drive. WILDERZAR reserved early on, made a steady advance three wide in the turn to loom in upper stretch, overtook the leader inside the eighth pole and was out-finished by the closing winner. QUESTION MARK prompted the pace through the turn, took command in upper stretch and finished evenly. ROYAL AIR FORCE stalked the pace from three wide down the backside, made an early bid to take the lead at the quarter pole and flattened out in the lane. ANGEL'S SOUPERSTAR showed brief speed to be the early pacesetter and gave way in the turn. KATZ ULTIMO was outrun.

ENTRY.NAME: Question Mark
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace, took command, even late

ENTRY.NAME: When in Rome
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, patient handling, angled 5w, determined

ENTRY.NAME: Wilderzar
ENTRY.COMMENT: steady advance, loomed upper, kept on, outfinished

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MAHONING VALLEY RACE COURSE RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 17600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAY ROYALITY set a well rated pace to the far turn, widened at will through the turn and pulled away easily in the lane as much best. MAUREENLOVESFRANK stalked the pace to the final turn, made a bid three wide nearing the quarter pole, failed to threaten the winner but kept on willingly to hold the place. POLYESTER BRIDE slow early to be at the rear of the field, commenced a rally midway on the far turn and kept grinding down the lane. ANIPPE prompted the pace for the first half and weakened. BACKSPLASH contended in good position down the backside and faded when lacking a response when called upon. QUEENOFCATNIPHILL was never a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, well rated, clear lead, easily, much best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MAHONING VALLEY RACE COURSE RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 12200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Ohio Registered Foals Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUANTUM THEORY reserved off the early pace racing three wide in the second flight, made a steady advance ranging up four wide in the turn, continued under a steady drive on the outside to pull clear in deep stretch. UNCAPTURED LYON tracked the pace down the backside, rallied midway on the bend in a drive and fought on through the lane to be up for second. CONSIDER ME prompted the early pace to the turn, assumed command on the bend, held the lead to midway down the lane and weakened inside the final eighth drifting out late. ON HIS TOES broke a step slow to give the field several lengths, continued to trail to the quarter pole and showed good late energy gaining through the stretch. SILVER MATT settled off the pace down the backstretch, rallied to contend in upper stretch and flattened out late. SEEING RED never seriously menaced. ARMOR PIERCING well placed early, dropped back on the bend and was never a threat. SECOND TO NO ONE stalked the pace to the turn, ranged up to be prominent at the quarter pole and gave way in the lane. ESTILO CLASICO showed brief speed from the fence and stopped turning for home.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke tardy, good late interest, gaining

ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace, assumed command, even late, weakened

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked, long drive, fought on, gained place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MAHONING VALLEY RACE COURSE RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14900. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Ohio Registered Foals Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHISKEY ROAN prompted the early pace through the first turn, settled off the pace down the backside, rallied into the far turn, idled through the turn losing position, angled six wide to the clear in upper stretch and kept coming down the lane to prevail late in a well managed ride. KING SOCIAL reserved off the early pace, rallied in the turn in a long drive to take command midway down the lane and was caught in the final fifty yards. MASTER set the pace while racing wide in the six path down the backside on a clear lead, battled to midway down the lane and weakened late in the drive. RUBINSTEIN well placed tracking the leaders through the final bend from the fence and failed to close in the stretch. LUCKY SMILE taken in hand to be at the rear of the field into the backstretch, chased from wide throughout and lacked a sufficient closing kick. FISHING FOR FUN raced prominently to the far turn, threatened on the bend and faded coming home. DUEL FUEL failed to menace.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MAHONING VALLEY RACE COURSE RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 54. Claiming Purse 19400. FOR REGISTERED OHIO BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAD BOY BOOGIE sped to the lead from the gate, opened a clear advantage entering the turn, was kept to task in the lane while unthreatened. CONSTITUTION COAL stalked the winner throughout, kept on willingly through the lane unable to challenge for the top prize while being second best in a good try. BIG TIME FLIRT chased the leaders, failed to gain on that pair but finished willingly as best of the rest. WHISKEY HELPS slow early to trail and made a steady advance down the lane to hit the board. GOOD MUSIC went evenly failing to mount a closing bid. NOSEY POWER raced mid-pack and failed to menace. CHILTEPIN prominently placed in the early going and steadily gave ground. BUCKEYE CHARLIE passed tiring rivals in the stretch. CANTRUNWITHBIGDOGS contended for the first half mile and gave way. YOU'RE OUT was never a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, clear lead, kept to task, unthreatened

ENTRY.NAME: Constitution Coal
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, kept on, no match, second best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MAHONING VALLEY RACE COURSE RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 75. Allowance Purse 25900. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 16 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances ).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DAWN slow early to be the distant trailer in a strung out field, rallied into the far turn circling five wide and closed well through the lane to be up in time. HONORABLE WOMAN set a pressured pace down the backside, shook clear of the presser into the far turn opening a clear advantage into upper stretch and was caught late in a good effort. SICILIAN STYLE TWO dueled with the pacesetter for five-eighths of a mile, could not go with that one and kept on evenly to hold the show. HIGH FASHION LADY tracked the leaders down the backside, made a mild rally in the turn but failed to gain ground. LADY GIULIANA chased the pacesetters to the far turn and faded. LITTLE EMPIRE was never a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Dawn
ENTRY.COMMENT: slow early, steady rally, circled 5w, closed well, in time

ENTRY.NAME: Honorable Woman
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace, cleared, caught late, good try

ENTRY.NAME: Sicilian Style Two
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled, pressed pace, no match, kept on evenly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Ohio Debutante S. MAHONING VALLEY RACE COURSE RACE 7 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 78. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD (OHIO ACCREDITED). $50 to nominate. $263 to enter and $487 to start with $75,000 Guaranteed. Purse to be divided 60% to the winner; 20% to second; 10% to third; 5% to fourth; 3% to fifth; 2% to sixth. Weig hts: Three-Year-Olds 122 lbs.; Older 124 lbs. Non-winners of a Sweepstakes at a mile or over in 2023 allowed 2 lbs.; Two races other than maiden, claiming or starter at a mile or over in 2023, 4 lbs. A race other than maiden, claiming or starter at a mile or over in 2023, 6 lbs. Starters to be named through the entry box Monday, November 13, 2023 by the usual time of closing. If more than eight (8) horses are entered this race will be run at One Mile and Seventy Yards. Trophy presented to the winning owne r.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOSSY LADY reserved off the pace saving ground for the first half mile, rallied four wide in the far turn through traffic, was taken in hand turning for home to dive to the rail behind the leaders, closed well up the fence in a determined drive to be up late in a well handled ride. AUNT BEE tracked the pace down the backside, split rivals in the turn to engage the leaders turning for home, took command in upper stretch and was run down late in the lane while clearly second best. NEAR PERFECT raced five wide down the backstretch while steadily gaining on the pacesetters, loomed up from five wide at the quarter pole to threaten in upper stretch and kept on through the lane to hold the show. KETTLE KISS worked her way to the inside to save ground down the backside, worked through traffic at the head of the lane and closed well belatedly. LUCKY PENNY ROSE slow early to be the distant trailer, picked up ground down the backside to be with the field, angled well wide circling the field coming home and closed willingly. EXPRESS FASHION saved ground along the fence while well placed in striking distance to the quarter pole and failed to gain ground in the lane. DIVA POWER pressed the pace to the three-eighths pole, assumed command on the turn and weakened coming home. SARAH JANE set the pace to the far turn under pressure and gave way at the head of the lane. LOFTY COWTOWN stalked the pace to the far turn, challenged from three wide at the quarter pole and tired in the stretch. STAR RULES failed to menace. GOODNESS SAKES prominently placed in the early going, dropped out of contention down the backside and passed tiring rivals down the lane. CHILLVILLE was never a threat. DRIVEN FOR SUCCESS was outrun.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIAL DIRECT pressed the pace in the early going, took command on the bend, opened a clear advantage and drew off in the stretch. GUNNER GABRIEL set the early pace under pressure, was overtaken on the bend and kept on through the lane to hold the show. GRAY TORMENTOR unhurried early to be near the rear of the field and never posed a threat. NOAH MY BABY contended early and steadily faded. AFFAIR TO REMEMBER was through early.
